title: Scott 750 Medium Frame 27,5
text: The Scott Spark 750 2015 mountain bike is designed for fast cross country rides and technical trails. The geometry and travel on the 6061 aluminium frame are designed for speed on the trails. Fly faster around trails and conquer singletrack with a fast, responsive frame. The list of components on this bike are also as competitive as the price, featuring 100mm Fox Evolution forks, hydraulic Shimano Deorre disc brakes, Shimano XT rear components. First the 6061 aluminium frame at the heart of this bike is both lightweight and responsive. With a light frame, and a short travel rear suspension unit, this bike will keep you firmly planted on technical trails and allow you to corner faster and beat your friends out of the woods. The Shimano gearing which features an XT rear mech and various Deore components offers a powerful balance of responsive shifting performance and long term durability. The XT rear mech will shift effortlessly even under strain and the 10 speed rear mech will provide enough gears for any hill or long day of riding. The gearing on this bike is also designed for long term durability and quality. The 100mm Fox Float forks will help to keep your front end planted on the trail. With a responsive rebound, these forks will keep up easily with bumpy terrain and provide you with a more planted, controlled and comfortable ride. Shimano M506 hydraulic disc brakes provide great stopping power so you will be able to ride faster and more confidently into corners and down steep descents knowing that you will be able to stop quickly when required. This is particularly beneficial in tight, technical situations where you have changing terrains and gradients. Finally this bike features 27.5" wheels. This wheel size provides the best of both worlds when it comes to off-road riding. Featuring the efficiency and performance of a larger wheel for cross country riding and nimble agility of a smaller wheel for tight, technical trails. title: Look 795 with ENVE 3.4 wheelset
text: Selling my 2016 Look 795 with ENVE 3.4 clincher wheelset, dura ace 9000 11-speed mechanical group set and Look pedals. This is the perfect bike for anyone looking at getting an aerodynamic lightweight (sub 7kg) racing bike.
